{{DISPLAYTITLE:Level 314: "Colorful Obstacles"}}

{{Class Variable}}
<center>[[Level 314]], named as '''"Colorful Obstacles,"''' is the 315th level of the Backrooms.</center>
== Description ==
The level manifests as an expansive, interconnected structure composed of vacant rooms, each fulfilled in with vivid, or unusual, and unnatural colorations. Located between a monotonous, and unchanging grey sky: the whole sky is sensed displaced from reality. Above or below, immense clouds roam slowly in uneven, unorganized patterns, their unnatural motion breaking any natural pattern, and rhythm, as if fragile frames of a looped, and glitched animation.

A smooth, playful cartoon melody is present through the atmosphere at all times. It subtly adjusts tempo based on the movements of those individuals within: fastening with sudden usages of high energy of one, and slowing with exhaustion of an individual. The sound becomes louder near walls, corners, and doorframes, as if its source is within the structure itself. Occasionally, the melody stutters or loops a rhythm oddly, usually moments before a strange behavior shifts of a room.

Rooms and chambers are interconnected by inert elevators, which no longer serve their intended function but strangely act as thresholds between spaces. Each room and chamber is saturated in a unique color palette, reflecting its distinct conditions, anomalies, and hazards, some are safe, and others are lethal. The environment responds in subtle but precise ways.
<br><br><br><br>
<tabber>
|-| Blue Palette=
== Blue Chamber ==
{{Blurimage|file=Level 211image.png|caption=Photograph taken before the appearance of the elevator doorway, whose photographer is unknown.}}
This uncommonly found chamber presents as a composition of layered blue hues, ranging from pale frost to deep cerulean, filling almost every emptiness with a cold feeling. A sterile brightness emanates from ceiling industrial LEDs, casting unnatural shadows and flattening depth. The air within the room is deceptively breathable at first, but may begin to thin rapidly after three to five minutes, which develops dizziness.

The atmosphere appears supernaturally still, and auditory perception is subtly dampened. Movement through the space causes a soft metallic reverb beneath an individual's footsteps. The cartoon melody, faint in most areas, here becomes muffled and off-tempo, and dragging sluggishly as the occupant begins to tire.

No clear exits are visible until a critical threshold of oxygen depletion is reached, at which point one of the non-functional elevators activates momentarily, and allowing escape for individuals. Unfortunate failure to reach it in time may result in one to unconsciousness or worse, although the exact consequences of full exposure is uncertain.

|-| Red Palette=
== Red Room ==
{{Blurimage|file=Level 211image2.png|caption=A rare red room only filled with stairs, and some tiny tripwires. The photographer's status is uncertainly alive.}}
Another uncommon room, usually sought after despite its peril, exhibits a colorations collection of deep crimson, scarlet, and rust-red shades saturating every surface. The air is sensed denser within, thick with tension, and the lighting shows a slight flicker, resembling somewhat a warning signal.

The room is crowded with physical obstacles: pillars, floating cubes, complex walls, non-functional doorframes, and several other more. Some of these objects reshape or rotate subtly when not in a perspective of one, which creates constantly changing paths. Others are anchored in place, forming tight corridors or unfortunate dead ends. Mechanical hazards are located throughout: crushers with very subtle sound, and false floor tiles dropping individuals onto metal ground with harmful depth. Hinged panels hide loaded spikes or sudden wall changes, which makes navigation much more extreme.

Despite these dangerous threats, the room is mostly stocked with plenty of resources. Metal lockers, storage crates, and supply cabinets are located in uneven random groups. Many contain chocolate bars, bottled [[Object 1|almond water]], or obscure tools, useful, but sometimes booby-trapped or locked behind dangerous mechanisms.

This red room is a combination of trial and reward. Individuals who navigate it carefully can leave the room equipped, but missteps, hesitation, or overconfidence are rarely forgiven.

|-| Purple Palette=
== Purple Room ==
This is the most commonly encountered room: a long corridor covered in a palette of muted violets and soft pinks. Dim lighting is illuminated across the space, which gives it a tranquil but surreal atmosphere. Minimal furnishings also decorated the corridor: short tables, empty bookshelves, chairs with rounded edges, and simple beds, each appearing gently changing in shade to match the room’s palette.

Despite their harmless appearance, the furniture exhibits subtle biomechanical signs. Their surfaces pulse slowly, as if breathing, faint, even expansions that betray an unnatural, semi-living sense. Physical contact with these furnitures causes immediate sensory phenomenon: a localized numbing effect that disables almost all of the sensation, including pain, across the region that contacted. AlThough frightening, this effect is temporary, fading away after approximately fifteen minutes without permanent harm to individuals.

Although it is not overly hostile, the deceptive calm and neuro-physical phenomena of this room make it a mixture of a place of rest and quiet risk.

|-| Green Palette=
== Green Chamber ==
This chamber is a frequently encountered chamber, characterised by multiple different green colorations that cover every surface. It is crowded with a group of juvenile collections: posters, toys, and miscellaneous play equipment, each appearing in the same verdant color. These items are not merely decorative; most exhibit faint luminescence and subtle visual distortions, as though partially unstable within the environment.

Gravity within the chamber is significantly weakened, which makes objects and individuals a slow, and buoyant movement when displaced. Movements are also sensed delayed, as if swimming in a dense fluid, and items thrown into the air descend with unnatural speed.

Placed throughout the chamber are unexpectedly useful supplies: canteens of [[Object 1|almond water]], energy bars, candies, health kits, batteries, and occasionally tools in fresh conditions. These useful items usually appear placed among the toys or hidden behind posters, as if deliberately placed. Their abundance and accessibility make the chamber a favored stop for individuals in need of quick replenishment.

Instead of an one elevator doorway, there are three to four of them that are closed, but automatically open upon an approach. Some of them lead to harmless, or even helpful rooms, and others direct to dangerous, and hostile environments.

|-| Brown Palette=
== Brown Room ==
This room is frequently encountered, appearing in a color palette of soft to dark brown shades that make the atmosphere feel like old wood and dry soil. The lighting is subdued in this room, reflecting warm amber colorations that never change in intensity. The walls and floors are smooth but harsh to the touch, resembling polished clay or pressed cardboard, and they emit a faint, earthy scent reminiscent of dried leaves or decaying paper.

Unlike other rooms and chambers, this one features no furnitures, hazards, or valuable resources. Its space is open, rectangular, and largely unremarkable aside from subtle environmental details: temperature is neutral and still, sound is heavily dampened, and footprints are took away by the floor, which gives the sense of walking through a preserved, and untouched exhibit.

|-| Rainbow Palette=
== Rainbow/Vivid Room ==
{{Blurimage|file=Level 211 drawing.png|caption=A witness illustration by a lost individual.}}
This room is easily recognizable by its radiant spectrum of color; walls and floor are painted in seamless gradients of every shade, and both sides of the room open directly into the motionless grey sky outside. Sunlight does not penetrate through the openings, but the room appears fully illuminated with an ethereal luminance.

Located midair at the center of the room is a stretched image of a modern, and classic clock, that is constantly ticking in unnatural rhythm. The ticking noises fill through the silence, heavy and deliberate, as if a heartbeat used for time. No elevator is present upon entry, However, when the clock hits exactly three o'clock, the atmosphere transitions rapidly: all color fades out from the room in seconds, fading out into a total grayscale room. At this state, an elevator quietly manifests, and the room enters a temporary altered state.

In this monochrome state, individuals may perceive a colossal grey entity crawling behind the clouds; its form subtly humanoid, but altered. It moves slowly on all fours, with its head loosely tethered to the sky by thin, wiry strings that beats like veins of a heart. The presence of this entity is usually connected to sharp migraines, spatial disorientation, and vivid hallucinations.

Placed across the room are groups of colorful but obviously artificial junk food: lukewarm hamburgers, soggy fries, melting candy, leaking soda cans, stale donuts, and frosted pastries. Although the food appears replenished after each visit, it brings no nutritional value and usually produces nausea, dizziness, or sluggishness when consumed.
</tabber>
<br><br><br><br>
== Entities ==
=== [[Hydrolitis Plague]] ===
Among the randomly placed consumables within the '''Rainbow Room''' or the '''Green Chamber''', numerous water bottles can be found, sealed, branded with old, and dirty labels, and appearing entirely ordinary at first glance. However, a small percentage of these containers are host to a parasitic, fluid-bound entity known as [[Hydrolitis Plague]].

=== Megalophobian ===
The colossal grey entities, which are seen only during the grayscale state of the '''Rainbow Room''', are theorized to be interdimensional custodians, silent, crawling figures bound to the sky by thin, string-like ligaments. They features long limbs and eyeless, sculpted faces that seem to rotate subtly, regardless of an individual's position. Although their movements are slow and barely perceptible, their mere presence exerts a psychoactive pressure, which triggers strong hallucinations and abstract emotional reactions: guilt, anticipation, or dread, with no clear source.

No direct interaction is documented, and it is currently unknown whether these beings are sentient, watching, or simply remnants of a forgotten process within the deeper architecture of the level. Researchers speculate that they are tied to the temporal structure of the level, possibly functioning as guardians or residents of cyclical resets governed by the central clock.
<br><br><br><br>
== Colonies, Bases, & Outposts ==
There are no known bases, outposts, or permanent habitations within this level. The unpredictability of room behaviors, coupled with the strange auditory loops and subtle environmental responses, makes any settlement unsustainable. Attempting to establish consistent shelter or communication networks has repeatedly failed, as rooms often change properties, rearrange themselves, or disappear entirely. Items left behind are frequently relocated, altered, or disappeared without warning. Due to those, individuals must remain transient, relying on caution, memory, and instinct as they navigate the strange geometry and unstable sensory landscape.
<br><br><br><br>
== Entrances & Exits ==
=== Entrances ===
* Entering a colorful door within [[Level 23]], [[Level 222]], or [[Level 450.1]], may lead to here.
* No-clipping through a unnaturally vivid wall in [[Level 119]], transports one to this level.
* Holding a childish tool in [[Level 14]], teleports an individual here.

=== Exits ===
* Finding a button then clicking it in the '''Red Room''', transitions this level to [[Level 100]].
* No-clipping through a dirty and less-saturated wall, leads to [[Level 600]].
* Jumping into the sky, obviously leads to [[The Void]].
* Prolonged staying inside the '''Rainbow Room''' after the timer hits three, transitions the level to [[Level 213]].
* Touching the purple potted plant in the '''Purple Room''' leads to [[level 626.2]].
